President Obama has declared a state of emergency in New Hampshire and ordered federal aid to assist with the aftermath of Hurricane Irene. This declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property. FEMA will have the authority to mobilize resources and equipment as needed. The federal government will provide 75 percent of funding for emergency protective measures. Craig A. Gilbert has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.